article.description: Shayla Scott had 14 points and 14 rebounds and Pittsburgh pulled away early in the second half for an 85-37 victory over West Virginia State on Saturday.
article.headline: Scott leads Pitt to win with 14 points, 14 boards
article.linkText: Scott's double-double leads way as Pitt rolls
article.story:
PITTSBURGH --  Shayla Scott had 14 points and 14 rebounds and Pittsburgh (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 16 AP) pulled away early in the second half for an 85-37 victory over West Virginia State on Saturday.

Kate Popovec added 17 points and 10 rebounds, and Taneisha Harrison had 15 points in the Panthers' first game since defeating then-No. 8 Maryland 86-57 on Sunday.

Pitt (7-1) led West Virginia State (5-3) by 36-22 at halftime, then began the second half with an 18-3 run to make it 54-25. The Panthers went on to outscore the Yellow Jackets 49-15 in the second half.

Shavonte Zellous had 10 points, six rebounds, five assists, two steals and two blocked shots for the Panthers. Pittsburgh held a 61-28 rebounding edge over the Division II Yellow Jackets.

Sandrea Coleman scored 12 points and Brittany Mingo had nine for West Virginia State, which was 14-of-64 from the field.
